interestingCommandDescription: LANG Records current position with tags. If position is already recorded it also can modify tags (add "-" in front of a tag to remove it). All positions will have tag called "places".
interestingCommandResult: LANG Recorded interesting place with tags [{0}].
interestingCommandExample1: LANG /interesting iron ore # records place with tags [iron] and [ore] (and also [place]).
interestingCommandExample2: LANG /interesting cat -dog # records place with tag [cat] and if place is already recorded removes its [dog] tag.
findInterestingPlaceCommandDescription: LANG Finds a recorded place that has given tags.
noMatchingPlacesFound: LANG No matching places found for tags {0}.
whatsSoInterestingCommandDescription: LANG Shows tags at this place.
noInterestingTagsFound: LANG There are no records for this place.
